<BaseLayout title="Privacy Policy">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-6">Privacy Policy</h1>

    <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-8">Last updated: November 1, 2025</p>

      <h2>Introduction</h2>
      <p>
        Nonprofit.ai ("we", "our", or "us") is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect information when you visit nonprofit.ai.
      </p>

      <h2>Information We Collect</h2>

      <h3>Analytics Data</h3>
      <p>
        We use Google Analytics to understand how visitors use our site. This includes:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Pages visited and time spent on site</li>
        <li>Browser type and device information</li>
        <li>General location (city/country level, not precise)</li>
        <li>How you arrived at our site (referrer)</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        This data is aggregated and anonymous. We cannot identify individual visitors.
      </p>

      <h3>Cookies</h3>
      <p>
        We use cookies for Google Analytics tracking. You can control cookies through our cookie consent banner and your browser settings. See our <a href="/cookies">Cookie Policy</a> for details.
      </p>

      <h2>Information We Do NOT Collect</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>We do not require accounts or logins</li>
        <li>We do not collect personal identifying information</li>
        <li>We do not track or store the prompts you copy</li>
        <li>We do not collect email addresses (unless you contact us)</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How We Use Information</h2>
      <p>
        Analytics data helps us:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Understand which prompts are most useful</li>
        <li>Improve site navigation and user experience</li>
        <li>Identify technical issues</li>
        <li>Make informed decisions about new content</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Third-Party Services</h2>
      <p>
        We use Google Analytics, which is operated by Google LLC. Google's privacy policy is available at <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">policies.google.com/privacy</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>Your Rights (GDPR)</h2>
      <p>
        If you are in the European Union, you have the right to:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Access your data</li>
        <li>Correct your data</li>
        <li>Delete your data</li>
        <li>Object to processing</li>
        <li>Data portability</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Since we collect minimal data through Google Analytics, you can exercise these rights by:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Declining cookies via our cookie consent banner</li>
        <li>Using browser privacy settings</li>
        <li>Installing Google Analytics opt-out browser extension</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Data Security</h2>
      <p>
        We take reasonable measures to protect data:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Site is served over HTTPS (encrypted connection)</li>
        <li>No user accounts means no password breaches</li>
        <li>Hosted on GitHub Pages with industry-standard security</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Children's Privacy</h2>
      <p>
        Our site is intended for nonprofit professionals (adults). We do not knowingly collect information from children under 13.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this Privacy Policy. Changes will be posted on this page with an updated date. Continued use of the site constitutes acceptance of changes.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about this Privacy Policy? Contact Leigh S. Ari√±o de la Rubia at <a href="mailto:Leigh.Arinodelarubia@gmail.com">Leigh.Arinodelarubia@gmail.com</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
